        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1973-10-08T19:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1973-10-08T19:10:00-05:00" n="133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <head>133. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassy in Lebanon<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d133fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 1173, <persName
                            corresp="#p_SHH_1">Harold H. Saunders</persName> Files, Middle East
                        Negotiations File, 1973 War, 9 October, 1973, File No. 4 [2 of 2]. Secret;
                        Niact; Immediate; Nodis. Drafted and approved by <persName corresp="#p_SJ_1"
                            >Sisco</persName>. Repeated Niact Immediate to Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1973-10-09T00:10:00+00:00">October 9, 1973,
                        0010Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>199794. Subject: Israeli Communication to Government of Lebanon. For Ambassador
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWB_1">Buffum</persName>. Secretary has received
                    following assur<pb facs="0427" n="392" xml:id="pg_392"/>ance from the Israeli
                        Government<note n="2" xml:id="d133fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> met with <persName
                            corresp="#p_DS_1">Dinitz</persName> from 6:40 to 7 p.m., October 8. Also
                        in this meeting, <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> assured
                            <persName corresp="#p_DS_1">Dinitz</persName> that Israel could load
                        electronic equipment on its plane. (Ibid., <gloss target="#t_RG_1"
                            >RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, <gloss target="#t_POL_1"
                            >POL</gloss> ISR–<gloss target="#t_US_1">US</gloss>)</note> which it
                    asked that we communicate to <gloss target="#t_GOL_1">GOL</gloss>: Israel has no
                    intention of violating Lebanese sovereignty provided Lebanon refrains from
                    military activity against Israel.<note n="3" xml:id="d133fn3">In telegram 11946
                        from Beirut, October 9, 1308Z, <persName corresp="#p_BWB_1"
                            >Buffum</persName> reported that he had transmitted the Israeli
                        assurances to Secretary General <persName corresp="#p_SN_1"
                            >Sadaqa</persName> of the Lebanese Foreign Office that morning and had
                        drawn his attention to the rapidity with which the Secretary personally had
                        taken up this matter with Israel. <persName corresp="#p_SN_1"
                            >Sadaqa</persName> said he was most appreciative of what the U.S.
                        Government had done. <persName corresp="#p_BWB_1">Buffum</persName> pointed
                        out that these assurances clearly implied that Lebanon had the
                        responsibility on its side to prevent military activity against Israel, and
                        he noted the seriousness of the fedayeen actions. (Ibid., <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 621, Country Files, Middle
                        East, Lebanon, Vol. III, Jan. 71–Oct. 72)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_KHA_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
